<procedure xmlns:dc="http://www.purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"
           xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
           xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
           xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
           xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.s1000d.org/S1000D_6/xml_schema_flat/proced.xsd">
  <identification>
    <title>Bicycle Stem Installation Procedure</title>
  </identification>
  <content>
    <section>
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <paragraph>This document details the procedure for installing a bicycle stem. It outlines preliminary requirements, the main procedure, and closing requirements.</paragraph>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Preliminary Requirements</title>
      <subsection>
        <title>Tools and Equipment</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <name>Clean Dry Cloth</name>
            <partNumber>KZ666</partNumber>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
          </item>
          <item>
            <name>Work Stand</name>
            <partNumber>KZ555</partNumber>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Supplies</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <name>Rubbing Alcohol</name>
            <partNumber>KZ222</partNumber>
            <quantity>1 Liter</quantity>
          </item>
          <item>
            <name>General Lubricant</name>
            <partNumber>KZ222</partNumber>
            <quantity>1 Liter</quantity>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Spares</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <name>Stem</name>
            <partNumber>KZ555</partNumber>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
          </item>
          <item>
            <name>Stem Bolt</name>
            <partNumber>KZ555</partNumber>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Safety Precautions</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <caution>Do not overtighten the stem bolt. Overtightening can damage the headset bearings.</caution>
          </item>
          <item>
            <caution>The stem bolt does not secure the stem.</caution>
          </item>
          <item>
            <note>Ensure the stem is aligned forward in line with the wheel.</note>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Prerequisites</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <description>Ensure the bicycle is securely mounted on a work stand with the front wheel free of the ground.</description>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Personnel</title>
        <list>
          <item>
            <name>Operator</name>
            <skillLevel>sk02</skillLevel>
            <estimatedTime>1 hour</estimatedTime>
            <category>Bike Rider</category>
          </item>
        </list>
      </subsection>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Main Procedure</title>
      <subsection>
        <title>Step 1: Cleaning</title>
        <paragraph>Remove all rust and corrosion using a clean dry cloth and rubbing alcohol.</paragraph>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Step 2: Stem Installation</title>
        <orderedList>
          <listItem>
            <title>Lubrication</title>
            <paragraph>Apply general lubricant to the following:</paragraph>
            <unorderedList>
              <listItem>The threads of the stem and stem bolt.</listItem>
              <listItem>The sides of the stem.</listItem>
              <listItem>The top of the wedge.</listItem>
            </unorderedList>
            <image>data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAj/U0AAAAASUVORK5CYII=</image>
            <note>Image placeholder – See original document for actual image</note>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <paragraph>Install the stem into the steerer tube.</paragraph>
            <image>data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAj/U0AAAAASUVORK5CYII=</image>
            <note>Image placeholder – See original document for actual image</note>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <title>Alignment &amp; Tightening</title>
            <paragraph>Adjust the stem to align with the wheel. Firmly tighten the stem bolt.</paragraph>
          </listItem>
        </orderedList>
      </subsection>
      <subsection>
        <title>Step 3: Handlebar Installation</title>
        <paragraph>Install the handlebars (refer to document: [S1000DBIKE, AAA, DA2, 2, 0, 00, AA, 720, A]).</paragraph>
      </subsection>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Closing Requirements</title>
      <paragraph>No specific closing requirements are listed.</paragraph>
    </section>
  </content>
</procedure>